The paper discusses a framework for robot teleoperation with Brain-Computer Interfaces (BCIs) that involves computer vision, user intent inference, and arbitration between human input and autonomous control schemes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on addressing challenges related to user control with BCIs, which suggests that it may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of computer vision and machine learning techniques to infer user intent and assist with control also suggests that the paper may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and/or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
